NOVEMBER 27, 2021, will never be easily forgotten by family members, friends and well-wishers as it was the day the late Vice President of Coscharis Group, Charity Nchedo Maduka, breathed her last on mother earth. The Night of Tributes held at Queen’s Park, Victoria Island, Lagos, presented an opportunity for relations, friends and Christian leaders to speak about Charity’s life and times. She was described as many things by different people. She was called a courageous woman, a true Christian and a force that held the Cosmas Maduka family together. She was finally laid to rest on January 7 at Maduka Residence, Coscharis Street, Umudimnkwa, Nnewi, Anambra State. Speaking at the Night of Tributes in Lagos, Cosmas Maduka said his late wife was a loving woman who gave boundless love, strength and care without discrimination.   How Uzoka started New Year     Modupe Sagoe turns 80     Alex-Duduyemi opens new house   “From the beginning of our journey, God faithfully led us for 43 years of love in an intimate relationship until November 27, 2021 when you peacefully went to sleep in the Lord. - Advertisement - “This date has become like 9/11 in my life, as I was obviously under heavy attack, because that is precisely what your sudden departure means to me. “The love we shared, however, gave birth to the institution that is today known as the Coscharis Group, and most importantly, the loving gift of five wonderful children, although we had to wait for six years before Cosmas junior was born.” The city of Nnewi, Anambra State, became busy for the burial ceremony. Traders, indigenes and residents came out en masse to witness the glorious exit of Charity.